 "incline_code": null,
 "intro_html": "Le Merinos (graded at least British 3c) makes up the first 3 pitches with an optional addition of the harder La Savonnette (4b). The route takes the west facing arete up the most northern of the Limestone outcrops at Freÿr. Overlooking the Meuse river in Wallonia, this is a classic 70m route which, due to its popularity is highly polished in places, especially the start. Adding La Savonnette as a 4th pitch take the route over 100m. The area is mixed climbing with old bolts and pitons that are best supplemented with a rack of nuts at a minimum.",
